# EC2 Instance Terraform Module

Terraform module to securely deploy an EC2 instance inside a VPC.

## ðŸ“¦ Features

- Deploy EC2 instances into public or private subnets
- SSH access restricted to specific CIDR ranges
- No public IP on private instances by default
- Full tagging support
- Exposes useful outputs like instance ID and IP

## ðŸ”§ Usage Example

```hcl
module "ec2_instance" {
  source = "../modules/ec2-instance"

  ami_id               = "ami-0123456789abcdef0"
  instance_type        = "t3.micro"
  subnet_id            = module.vpc.public_subnet_ids[0]
  vpc_id               = module.vpc.vpc_id
  key_name             = "my-ssh-key"
  instance_name        = "secure-instance"
  associate_public_ip  = true
  ssh_allowed_cidrs    = ["203.0.113.0/24"]

  tags = {
    Environment = "dev"
    Terraform   = "true"
  }
}

